- # Minimal layout for the in-Canvas LTI iframe views. Deliberately does NOT
- # render `shared/head`: these tiny chrome-less pages don't need the full
- # dashboard head, and loading it (the whole `main` CSS bundle, two external
- # Google Fonts stylesheets, and the vendors / i18n / Sentry JS bundles) made
- # the iframe slow to load and flash unstyled text while the webfont swapped
- # in. Instead we load one small dedicated CSS bundle (`lti_iframe`, a
- # render-blocking <link> so content is styled on first paint) and no app JS —
- # the couple of interactive views carry their own small inline scripts. The
- # navbar/footer are omitted too: the navbar reads `current_user`, which is
- # always logged-out inside the partitioned Canvas iframe.
!!!
%html{ dir: rtl? ? 'rtl' : nil, lang: I18n.locale }
  %head
    %meta{ charset: 'utf-8' }
    %meta{ content: 'width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0', name: 'viewport' }
    %title= raw ENV['dashboard_title'].to_s
    = logo_favicon_tag
    = dashboard_stylesheet_tag('lti_iframe')
    = csrf_meta_tags
  %body.lti-iframe
    %main.lti-iframe__main{ role: 'main' }
      = yield
